<TITLE> Police enjoy greater public trust than before: IGP </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chandpur, Sept 27 (bdnews24.com)  Inspector general of police Noor Mohammad said Thursday people's confidence in the police is higher than ever before. "We will introduce model police stations to make the police more multi-dimensional and modern," Noor said in his address as chief guest to a question-and-answer session held at Hasan Ali Government High School in Chandpur. The country's police chief added that the police planned to set up 17 model police stations to achieve their goals. "The police have been asked to stay extra vigilant regarding the law and order situation in the country during the Eid and Puja celebrations," Noor said. bdnews2
